{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Most of the time, art and science stare at each other"},{"time":4000,"text":"across a gulf of mutual incomprehension."},{"time":7000,"text":"There is great confusion when the two look at each other."},{"time":12000,"text":"Art, of course, looks at the world through the psyche,"},{"time":16000,"text":"the emotions -- the unconscious at times -- and of course the aesthetic."},{"time":20000,"text":"Science tends to look at the world through the rational, the quantitative --"},{"time":25000,"text":"things that can be measured and described --"},{"time":28000,"text":"but it gives art a terrific context of understanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"In the Extreme Ice Survey,"},{"time":36000,"text":"we're dedicated to bringing those two parts of human understanding together,"},{"time":41000,"text":"to merging the art and science"},{"time":43000,"text":"to the end of helping us understand nature"},{"time":46000,"text":"and humanity's relationship with nature better."},{"time":50000,"text":"Specifically, I as a person"},{"time":52000,"text":"who's been a professional nature photographer my whole adult life,"},{"time":56000,"text":"am firmly of the belief that photography, video, film"},{"time":60000,"text":"have tremendous powers for helping us understand"},{"time":64000,"text":"and shape the way we think about nature"},{"time":67000,"text":"and about ourselves in relationship to nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70000,"text":"In this project, we're specifically interested, of course, in ice."},{"time":74000,"text":"I'm fascinated by the beauty of it, the mutability of it,"},{"time":78000,"text":"the malleability of it,"},{"time":80000,"text":"and the fabulous shapes in which it can carve itself."},{"time":83000,"text":"These first images are from Greenland."},{"time":85000,"text":"But ice has another meaning."},{"time":87000,"text":"Ice is the canary in the global coal mine."},{"time":90000,"text":"It's the place where we can see and touch and hear and feel climate change in action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"Climate change is a really abstract thing in most of the world."},{"time":100000,"text":"Whether or not you believe in it is based on your sense of"},{"time":103000,"text":"is it raining more or is it raining less?"},{"time":105000,"text":"Is it getting hotter or is it getting colder?"},{"time":107000,"text":"What do the computer models say about this, that and the other thing?"},{"time":112000,"text":"All of that, strip it away. In the world of the arctic and alpine environments,"},{"time":116000,"text":"where the ice is, it's real and it's present."},{"time":119000,"text":"The changes are happening. They're very visible."},{"time":122000,"text":"They're photographable. They're measurable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"95 percent of the glaciers in the world are retreating or shrinking."},{"time":130000,"text":"That's outside Antarctica."},{"time":132000,"text":"95 percent of the glaciers in the world are retreating or shrinking,"},{"time":135000,"text":"and that's because the precipitation patterns and the temperature patterns are changing."},{"time":139000,"text":"There is no significant scientific dispute about that."},{"time":143000,"text":"It's been observed, it's measured, it's bomb-proof information."},{"time":146000,"text":"And the great irony and tragedy of our time"},{"time":148000,"text":"is that a lot of the general public thinks that science is still arguing about that."},{"time":153000,"text":"Science is not arguing about that."},{"time":155000,"text":"In these images we see ice from enormous glaciers,"},{"time":160000,"text":"ice sheets that are hundreds of thousands of years old"},{"time":162000,"text":"breaking up into chunks, and chunk by chunk by chunk,"},{"time":166000,"text":"iceberg by iceberg, turning into global sea level rise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"So, having seen all of this in the course of a 30-year career,"},{"time":173000,"text":"I was still a skeptic about climate change until about 10 years ago,"},{"time":176000,"text":"because I thought the story of climate change was based on computer models."},{"time":182000,"text":"I hadn't realized it was based on concrete measurements"},{"time":186000,"text":"of what the paleoclimates -- the ancient climates -- were,"},{"time":189000,"text":"as recorded in the ice sheets, as recorded in deep ocean sediments,"},{"time":195000,"text":"as recorded in lake sediments, tree rings,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and a lot of other ways of measuring temperature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"When I realized that climate change was real, and it was not based on computer models,"},{"time":206000,"text":"I decided that one day I would do a project"},{"time":208000,"text":"looking at trying to manifest climate change photographically."},{"time":212000,"text":"And that led me to this project."},{"time":215000,"text":"Initially, I was working on a National Geographic assignment --"},{"time":218000,"text":"conventional, single frame, still photography."},{"time":220000,"text":"And one crazy day, I got the idea that I should --"},{"time":224000,"text":"after that assignment was finished --"},{"time":226000,"text":"I got the idea that I should shoot in time-lapse photography,"},{"time":230000,"text":"that I should station a camera or two at a glacier"},{"time":234000,"text":"and let it shoot every 15 minutes, or every hour or whatever"},{"time":237000,"text":"and watch the progression of the landscape over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"Well, within about three weeks,"},{"time":243000,"text":"I incautiously turned that idea of a couple of time-lapse cameras"},{"time":246000,"text":"into 25 time-lapse cameras."},{"time":248000,"text":"And the next six months of my life were the hardest time in my career,"},{"time":253000,"text":"trying to design, build and deploy out in the field these 25 time-lapse cameras."},{"time":259000,"text":"They are powered by the sun. Solar panels power them."},{"time":263000,"text":"Power goes into a battery. There is a custom made computer"},{"time":266000,"text":"that tells the camera when to fire."},{"time":269000,"text":"And these cameras are positioned on rocks on the sides of the glaciers,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and they look in on the glacier from permanent, bedrock positions,"},{"time":276000,"text":"and they watch the evolution of the landscape."},{"time":279000,"text":"We just had a number of cameras out on the Greenland Ice Sheet."},{"time":282000,"text":"We actually drilled holes into the ice, way deep down below the thawing level,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and had some cameras out there for the past month and a half or so."},{"time":290000,"text":"Actually, there's still a camera out there right now."},{"time":292000,"text":"In any case, the cameras shoot roughly every hour."},{"time":295000,"text":"Some of them shoot every half hour, every 15 minutes, every five minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Here's a time lapse of one of the time-lapse units being made."},{"time":302000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":304000,"text":"I personally obsessed about every nut, bolt and washer in these crazy things."},{"time":308000,"text":"I spent half my life at our local hardware store"},{"time":310000,"text":"during the months when we built these units originally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"We're working in most of the major glaciated regions of the northern hemisphere."},{"time":321000,"text":"Our time-lapse units are in Alaska, the Rockies, Greenland and Iceland,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and we have repeat photography positions,"},{"time":327000,"text":"that is places we just visit on an annual basis,"},{"time":330000,"text":"in British Columbia, the Alps and Bolivia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"It's a big undertaking. I stand here before you tonight"},{"time":335000,"text":"as an ambassador for my whole team."},{"time":338000,"text":"There's a lot of people working on this right now."},{"time":340000,"text":"We've got 33 cameras out this moment."},{"time":343000,"text":"We just had 33 cameras shoot about half an hour ago"},{"time":347000,"text":"all across the northern hemisphere, watching what's happened."},{"time":350000,"text":"And we've spent a lot of time in the field. It's been a fantastic amount of work."},{"time":354000,"text":"We've been out for two and a half years,"},{"time":356000,"text":"and we've got about another two and a half years yet to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358000,"text":"That's only half our job."},{"time":360000,"text":"The other half of our job is to tell the story to the global public."},{"time":364000,"text":"You know, scientists have collected this kind of information"},{"time":369000,"text":"off and on over the years, but a lot of it stays within the science community."},{"time":374000,"text":"Similarly, a lot of art projects stay in the art community,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and I feel very much a responsibility through mechanisms like TED,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and like our relationship with the Obama White House,"},{"time":387000,"text":"with the Senate, with John Kerry, to influence policy"},{"time":391000,"text":"as much as possible with these pictures as well."},{"time":393000,"text":"We've done films. We've done books. We have more coming."},{"time":397000,"text":"We have a site on Google Earth"},{"time":399000,"text":"that Google Earth was generous enough to give us,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and so forth, because we feel very much the need to tell this story,"},{"time":406000,"text":"because it is such an immediate evidence of ongoing climate change right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"Now, one bit of science before we get into the visuals."},{"time":416000,"text":"If everybody in the developed world understood this graph,"},{"time":420000,"text":"and emblazoned it on the inside of their foreheads,"},{"time":423000,"text":"there would be no further societal argument about climate change"},{"time":427000,"text":"because this is the story that counts."},{"time":430000,"text":"Everything else you hear is just propaganda and confusion."},{"time":434000,"text":"Key issues: this is a 400,000 year record."},{"time":437000,"text":"This exact same pattern is seen going back now"},{"time":439000,"text":"almost a million years before our current time."},{"time":442000,"text":"And several things are important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"Number one: temperature and carbon dioxide in the atmosphere"},{"time":448000,"text":"go up and down basically in sync."},{"time":450000,"text":"You can see that from the orange line and the blue line."},{"time":453000,"text":"Nature naturally has allowed carbon dioxide to go up to 280 parts per million."},{"time":460000,"text":"That's the natural cycle."},{"time":462000,"text":"Goes up to 280 and then drops"},{"time":464000,"text":"for various reasons that aren't important to discuss right here."},{"time":467000,"text":"But 280 is the peak."},{"time":469000,"text":"Right now, if you look at the top right part of that graph,"},{"time":472000,"text":"we're at 385 parts per million."},{"time":474000,"text":"We are way, way outside the normal, natural variability."},{"time":479000,"text":"Earth is having a fever."},{"time":481000,"text":"In the past hundred years, the temperature of the Earth"},{"time":484000,"text":"has gone up 1.3 degrees Fahrenheit, .75 degrees Celsius,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and it's going to keep going up"},{"time":491000,"text":"because we keep dumping fossil fuels into the atmosphere."},{"time":494000,"text":"At the rate of about two and a half parts per million per year."},{"time":497000,"text":"It's been a remorseless, steady increase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"We have to turn that around."},{"time":502000,"text":"That's the crux, and someday I hope to emblazon that"},{"time":505000,"text":"across Times Square in New York and a lot of other places."},{"time":508000,"text":"But anyway, off to the world of ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"We're now at the Columbia Glacier in Alaska."},{"time":512000,"text":"This is a view of what's called the calving face."},{"time":515000,"text":"This is what one of our cameras saw over the course of a few months."},{"time":518000,"text":"You see the glacier flowing in from the right,"},{"time":522000,"text":"dropping off into the sea, camera shooting every hour."},{"time":525000,"text":"If you look in the middle background,"},{"time":527000,"text":"you can see the calving face bobbing up and down like a yo-yo."},{"time":531000,"text":"That means that glacier's floating and it's unstable,"},{"time":534000,"text":"and you're about to see the consequences of that floating."},{"time":537000,"text":"To give you a little bit of a sense of scale,"},{"time":540000,"text":"that calving face in this picture"},{"time":542000,"text":"is about 325 feet tall. That's 32 stories."},{"time":547000,"text":"This is not a little cliff. This is like a major office building in an urban center."},{"time":552000,"text":"The calving face is the wall where the visible ice breaks off,"},{"time":557000,"text":"but in fact, it goes down below sea level another couple thousand feet."},{"time":562000,"text":"So there's a wall of ice a couple thousand feet deep"},{"time":566000,"text":"going down to bedrock if the glacier's grounded on bedrock,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and floating if it isn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"Here's what Columbia's done. This is in south central Alaska."},{"time":578000,"text":"This was an aerial picture I did one day in June three years ago."},{"time":583000,"text":"This is an aerial picture we did this year."},{"time":586000,"text":"That's the retreat of this glacier."},{"time":589000,"text":"The main stem, the main flow of the glacier is coming from the right"},{"time":593000,"text":"and it's going very rapidly up that stem."},{"time":596000,"text":"We're going to be up there in just a few more weeks,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and we expect that it's probably retreated another half a mile,"},{"time":603000,"text":"but if I got there and discovered that it had collapsed"},{"time":606000,"text":"and it was five miles further back, I wouldn't be the least bit surprised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Now it's really hard to grasp the scale of these places,"},{"time":614000,"text":"because as the glaciers --"},{"time":616000,"text":"one of the things is that places like Alaska and Greenland are huge,"},{"time":619000,"text":"they're not normal landscapes --"},{"time":621000,"text":"but as the glaciers are retreating, they're also deflating,"},{"time":625000,"text":"like air is being let out of a balloon."},{"time":628000,"text":"And so, there are features on this landscape."},{"time":631000,"text":"There's a ridge right in the middle of the picture, up above where that arrow comes in,"},{"time":635000,"text":"that shows you that a little bit."},{"time":637000,"text":"There's a marker line called the trim line"},{"time":640000,"text":"above our little red illustration there."},{"time":644000,"text":"This is something no self-respecting photographer would ever do --"},{"time":646000,"text":"you put some cheesy illustration on your shot, right? --"},{"time":649000,"text":"and yet you have to do it sometimes to narrate these points."},{"time":653000,"text":"But, in any case, the deflation of this glacier since 1984"},{"time":657000,"text":"has been higher than the Eiffel Tower, higher than the Empire State Building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"A tremendous amount of ice has been let out of these valleys"},{"time":665000,"text":"as it's retreated and deflated, gone back up valley."},{"time":670000,"text":"These changes in the alpine world are accelerating."},{"time":673000,"text":"It's not static."},{"time":675000,"text":"Particularly in the world of sea ice,"},{"time":678000,"text":"the rate of natural change is outstripping predictions of just a few years ago,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and the processes either are accelerating"},{"time":685000,"text":"or the predictions were too low to begin with."},{"time":687000,"text":"But in any case, there are big, big changes happening as we speak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"So, here's another time-lapse shot of Columbia."},{"time":696000,"text":"And you see where it ended in these various spring days,"},{"time":699000,"text":"June, May, then October."},{"time":701000,"text":"Now we turn on our time lapse."},{"time":703000,"text":"This camera was shooting every hour."},{"time":705000,"text":"Geologic process in action here."},{"time":707000,"text":"And everybody says, well don't they advance in the winter time?"},{"time":710000,"text":"No. It was retreating through the winter because it's an unhealthy glacier."},{"time":713000,"text":"Finally catches up to itself, it advances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"And you can look at these pictures over and over again"},{"time":722000,"text":"because there's such a strange, bizarre fascination in seeing"},{"time":726000,"text":"these things you don't normally get to see come alive."},{"time":729000,"text":"We've been talking about \"seeing is believing \""},{"time":731000,"text":"and seeing the unseen at TED Global."},{"time":734000,"text":"That's what you see with these cameras."},{"time":737000,"text":"The images make the invisible visible."},{"time":744000,"text":"These huge crevasses open up."},{"time":746000,"text":"These great ice islands break off --"},{"time":749000,"text":"and now watch this."},{"time":751000,"text":"This has been the springtime this year --"},{"time":759000,"text":"a huge collapse. That happened in about a month,"},{"time":761000,"text":"the loss of all that ice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"So that's where we started three years ago,"},{"time":775000,"text":"way out on the left, and that's where we were a few months ago, the"},{"time":777000,"text":"last time we went into Columbia."},{"time":780000,"text":"To give you a feeling for the scale of the retreat,"},{"time":782000,"text":"we did another cheesy illustration,"},{"time":784000,"text":"with British double-decker buses."},{"time":787000,"text":"If you line up 295 of those nose to tail, that's about how far back that was."},{"time":792000,"text":"It's a long way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797000,"text":"On up to Iceland."},{"time":799000,"text":"One of my favorite glaciers, the Sólheimajökull."},{"time":805000,"text":"And here, if you watch, you can see the terminus retreating."},{"time":808000,"text":"You can see this river being formed."},{"time":810000,"text":"You can see it deflating."},{"time":818000,"text":"Without the photographic process, you would never see this. This is invisible."},{"time":822000,"text":"You can stand up there your whole life and you would never see this,"},{"time":825000,"text":"but the camera records it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"So we wind time backwards now."},{"time":835000,"text":"We go back a couple years in time."},{"time":837000,"text":"That's where it started."},{"time":845000,"text":"That's where it ended a few months ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"And on up to Greenland."},{"time":853000,"text":"The smaller the ice mass, the faster it responds to climate."},{"time":857000,"text":"Greenland took a little while to start reacting"},{"time":860000,"text":"to the warming climate of the past century,"},{"time":863000,"text":"but it really started galloping along about 20 years ago."},{"time":867000,"text":"And there's been a tremendous increase in the temperature up there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"It's a big place. That's all ice."},{"time":872000,"text":"All those colors are ice and it goes up to about two miles thick,"},{"time":876000,"text":"just a gigantic dome that comes in from the coast and rises in the middle."},{"time":880000,"text":"The one glacier up in Greenland"},{"time":882000,"text":"that puts more ice into the global ocean"},{"time":884000,"text":"than all the other glaciers in the northern hemisphere combined"},{"time":887000,"text":"is the Ilulissat Glacier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889000,"text":"We have some cameras on the south edge of the Ilulissat,"},{"time":892000,"text":"watching the calving face as it goes through this dramatic retreat."},{"time":896000,"text":"Here's a two-year record of what that looks like."},{"time":898000,"text":"Helicopter in front of the calving face for scale, quickly dwarfed."},{"time":903000,"text":"The calving face is four and a half miles across,"},{"time":905000,"text":"and in this shot, as we pull back, you're only seeing about a mile and a half."},{"time":908000,"text":"So, imagine how big this is"},{"time":910000,"text":"and how much ice is charging out."},{"time":912000,"text":"The interior of Greenland is to the right."},{"time":914000,"text":"It's flowing out to the Atlantic Ocean on the left."},{"time":917000,"text":"Icebergs, many, many, many, many times the size of this building, are roaring out to sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"We just downloaded these pictures a couple weeks ago,"},{"time":925000,"text":"as you can see. June 25th,"},{"time":929000,"text":"monster calving events happened."},{"time":931000,"text":"I'll show you one of those in a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"This glacier has doubled its flow speed in the past 15 years."},{"time":938000,"text":"It now goes at 125 feet a day, dumping all this ice into the ocean."},{"time":943000,"text":"It tends to go in these pulses, about every three days,"},{"time":945000,"text":"but on average, 125 feet a day,"},{"time":947000,"text":"twice the rate it did 20 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"Okay. We had a team out watching this glacier,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and we recorded the biggest calving event that's ever been put on film."},{"time":958000,"text":"We had nine cameras going."},{"time":960000,"text":"This is what a couple of the cameras saw."},{"time":964000,"text":"A 400-foot-tall calving face breaking off."},{"time":968000,"text":"Huge icebergs rolling over."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Okay, how big was that? It's hard to get it."},{"time":1018000,"text":"So an illustration again, gives you a feeling for scale."},{"time":1021000,"text":"A mile of retreat in 75 minutes"},{"time":1024000,"text":"across the calving face, in that particular event, three miles wide."},{"time":1028000,"text":"The block was three-fifths of a mile deep,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"and if you compare the expanse of the calving face"},{"time":1033000,"text":"to the Tower Bridge in London, about 20 bridges wide."},{"time":1036000,"text":"Or if you take an American reference, to the U.S. Capitol Building"},{"time":1040000,"text":"and you pack 3,000 Capitol Buildings into that block,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"it would be equivalent to how large that block was."},{"time":1049000,"text":"75 minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053000,"text":"Now I've come to the conclusion"},{"time":1055000,"text":"after spending a lot of time in this climate change world"},{"time":1058000,"text":"that we don't have a problem of economics, technology and public policy."},{"time":1062000,"text":"We have a problem of perception."},{"time":1065000,"text":"The policy and the economics and the technology are serious enough issues,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"but we actually can deal with them."},{"time":1070000,"text":"I'm certain that we can."},{"time":1073000,"text":"But what we have is a perception problem"},{"time":1075000,"text":"because not enough people really get it yet."},{"time":1079000,"text":"You're an elite audience. You get it."},{"time":1081000,"text":"Fortunately, a lot of the political leaders in the major countries of the world"},{"time":1085000,"text":"are an elite audience that for the most part gets it now."},{"time":1089000,"text":"But we still need to bring a lot of people along with us."},{"time":1092000,"text":"And that's where I think organizations like TED,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"like the Extreme Ice Survey can have a terrific impact"},{"time":1099000,"text":"on human perception and bring us along."},{"time":1102000,"text":"Because I believe we have an opportunity right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"We are nearly on the edge of a crisis,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"but we still have an opportunity to face the greatest challenge"},{"time":1111000,"text":"of our generation and, in fact, of our century."},{"time":1114000,"text":"This is a terrific, terrific call to arms"},{"time":1118000,"text":"to do the right thing for ourselves and for the future."},{"time":1121000,"text":"I hope that we have the wisdom to let the angels of our better nature"},{"time":1124000,"text":"rise to the occasion and do what needs to be done. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1128000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}